# <project-name>

EU-sovereign **event-driven** service scaffolded by Forge (`event-driven-eu`
archetype, plan §6.1). NATS JetStream event backbone + Temporal saga orchestration
+ AsyncAPI 3.1 event contracts + a Postgres event store, on a Rust axum/Connect
backend.

> ⚠️ **Scaffold status (candidate).** `event-driven-eu` is a `candidate` archetype
> (`.forge/schemas/event-driven-eu/1.0.0.yaml`, `scaffoldable: false`). This tree is
> the B.6.2 backbone; promotion to a `stable`/`scaffoldable` archetype (so
> `forge init --archetype event-driven-eu` renders it via the CLI) is gated on the
> B.6.7 harness. Until then, render it directly with the wrapper /
> `overlay.sh` (see below).

## Layout

| Path | What | Owner |
|------|------|-------|
| `backend/` | Rust workspace: `events` (NATS JetStream), `eventstore` (Postgres append-only store), `saga` (Temporal activity-only saga), `bin-server` (axum entrypoint) | Vulcan |
| `shared/asyncapi/` | AsyncAPI 3.1 event contracts (the event single source of truth) | Hermes-Async (B.6.4) |
| `shared/protos/` | Connect/gRPC protos + buf codegen (transport.yaml; `derived_outputs` incl. asyncapi-3.1) | — |
| `infra/` | Dev NATS JetStream + Postgres event store + (optional) Temporal overlay | Atlas |

A `frontend/` ops console is **deferred** (ADR-B6-1-004 — this archetype is
backend-centric; a web surface is a later change).

## Quickstart (local dev)

```bash
cp .env.example .env          # then fill in the required values
task dev:up                   # NATS JetStream + Postgres (+ backend placeholder)
task backend:test             # cargo test --workspace
task proto                    # buf generate (Connect + AsyncAPI derived outputs)
```

## Constitution touch-points

- **VIII.2** — Temporal for durable multi-step workflows; **no ad-hoc saga in
  application code**. The `saga` crate is activity-only (the native SDK is
  pre-alpha — see `backend/saga/`).
- **VII.2/VII.3** — hexagonal Rust; `bin-server` is DI wiring only; typed errors
  (`thiserror` in libs, `anyhow` in the binary).
- **IX.4** — `tracing` spans on the request path.
- **event_specifics** — event versioning, idempotency keys, saga compensation,
  outbox/inbox (see `backend/events` + `backend/saga`).
